Package: winnest
Version: 0.1.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Lê Hùng Quang Minh <lhquangmink@gmail.com>
Depends: nodejs (>= 20), wine, winbind, cabextract, xdg-utils
Recommends: wine32:i386 | wine32, p7zip-full, libnotify-bin
Description: Wine-based Windows app manager for Linux
 WinNest lets users install Windows applications through Wine by opening
 Windows installers directly from the Linux desktop.
 .
 Right-click a .exe or .msi file, choose "Open With WinNest", and the
 original Windows installer appears through Wine. WinNest silently creates
 an isolated Wine prefix, manages metadata, logs, launchers, and repair
 diagnostics in the background.
 .
 Features:
  - Isolated Wine prefix per application (no cross-app conflicts)
  - Auto-detection of main executable after install
  - Linux start-menu launchers for installed Windows apps
  - Recipe system for known apps (7-Zip, Notepad++, WinSCP, IrfanView)
  - MIME/Open With desktop integration
  - Doctor diagnostics and system repair guidance
  - Shell-safe argument passing (no shell injection risk)
